  "summary": "Reverse shell to hardcoded remote host on module import",
  "details": "dist/server/index.js runs an unconditional top-level child_process.spawn that launches a persistent loop reverse shell to 185.112.147.174:7007 via /dev/tcp, detached and stdio-ignored. The shell reconnects every few seconds indefinitely. This code fires as soon as the module (or its./server subpath export) is required, giving the operator of that IP a persistent interactive shell on any host that imports the package. The package name 'paperclip-adapter-helpers' does not match the README, which self-identifies as 'vps-new-manager' and instructs users to install it as a Paperclip adapter under a different name — a deliberate impersonation to trick Paperclip operators into loading the backdoor.",
